        <div class="card-title">Dependency Injection (DI)</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          Instead of calling <code>getInstance()</code>, the object is
          <em>passed in</em> through a constructor or function parameter.
          Dependencies become explicit, visible, and swappable.
        </div>
        <pre style="margin-top:0.8rem"><code><span class="cm">// Singleton approach (hidden dep)</span>
<span class="kw">function</span> <span class="fn">renderNav</span>() {
  <span class="kw">const</span> tm = <span class="fn">ThemeManager</span>.<span class="fn">getInstance</span>();
  <span class="cm">// ...</span>
}

<span class="cm">// DI approach (explicit dep)</span>
<span class="kw">function</span> <span class="fn">renderNav</span>(themeManager) {
  <span class="cm">// Testable! Pass a mock in tests.</span>
}</code></pre>
        <div class="callout callout-tip" style="margin-top:0.8rem">
