<!-- ── Hero ── -->
<div class="hero">
  <span class="hero-badge">Design Pattern</span>
  <h1>Singleton Theme Manager</h1>
  <p>
    A practical demonstration of the <strong>Singleton pattern</strong> managing
    application-wide theme state — with an honest discussion of its trade-offs.
  </p>
  <div class="hero-actions">
    <a href="#demo" class="btn btn-primary">View Demo</a>
    <a href="#discussion" class="btn btn-outline">Read Discussion</a>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">

  <!-- ── Overview Cards ── -->
  <section id="overview">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>What is the Singleton Pattern?</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <p>Ensures a class has only one instance and provides a global access point to it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cards-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card-icon">🔒</span>
        <h3>Single Instance</h3>
        <p>Only one ThemeManager object ever exists in memory. Every call to <code>getInstance()</code> returns the exact same object reference.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card-icon">🌐</span>
        <h3>Global Access Point</h3>
        <p>Any module in your app can access the theme state without passing references through props or function arguments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card-icon">⚡</span>
        <h3>Lazy Initialization</h3>
        <p>The instance is created only when first requested, avoiding unnecessary memory allocation at startup.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card-icon">📡</span>
        <h3>Observer Ready</h3>
        <p>Easily extended with the Observer pattern so components can subscribe to theme changes reactively.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Stats ── -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>Pattern at a Glance</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="stats-grid">
      <div class="stat-card">
        <span class="stat-value" id="instanceCount">1</span>
        <div class="stat-label">Active Instances</div>
      </div>
