### What's in the file

| Area | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Singleton** | `ThemeManager` uses a private static `#instance` field; the constructor throws if called directly after first instantiation |
| **Theme persistence** | Reads `localStorage` on init, falls back to `prefers-color-scheme`, then hard-coded `"light"` |
| **CSS bridge** | A single `data-theme` attribute on `<html>` drives ~30 CSS custom properties; every element transitions automatically |
| **Observer hook** | `subscribe(fn)` lets any UI widget react to theme changes without polling |
| **UI coverage** | Header/nav, hero, feature cards, alerts (4 variants), buttons (5 variants), tags, progress bars, form inputs, data table, syntax-highlighted code block, footer, toast notification |
| **Discussion section** | Inline rendered pros/cons lists, when-to-use-DI guidance, and a verdict — all theme-aware |
| **Console demos** | Logs `a === b → true` and the constructor guard error so you can inspect the singleton guarantee in DevTools |

